Article Example of Clean Water Problems: America’s Failing Drinking Water System

Key Points: Chronic underinvestment has left water infrastructure outdated and on the verge of collapse in many places across the country. 
Example: historic flooding last summer damaged operations at a water treatment plant in Jackson, Mississippi, leaving more than 150,000 people without safe drinking water for weeks.

Key Points: Substances known as PFAS, industrial pollution, and agricultural runoff are contaminating the drinking water for hundreds of millions of people and many don’t even know it.
Example: In Buffalo, New York, 64% of houses are more than 80 years old, giving the city the distinction of having the oldest urban housing stock in the United States. Unfortunately, the pipes that bring water to those homes are often just as old, exposing many residents to lead, a neurotoxin. Nearly 6%of Buffalo’s children have elevated lead levels in their blood, which is triple the exposure rate of Flint, Michigan.

